1 application. To determine the competency of applicants, the commission shall
2 prescribe and hold examinations at designated times and places.
3 2. In addition to the requirements established by subsection 1, an applicant for a broker's
4 or salesperson's license must be at least eighteen years of age.
5 3. Every applicant for a license as a real estate broker:
6 a. Must have been actively engaged as a licensed real estate salesperson for a
7 period of at least two years preceding the date of application; or
8 b. Must have had experience as determined by the commission to be substantially
9 equal to that which a licensed real estate salesperson would ordinarily receive
10 during a period of two years.
11 4. As a prerequisite for licensure, an applicant for a salesperson's license shall furnish to
12 the commission evidence the applicant has successfully completed at least ninety
13 hours in courses of study approved by the commission. An applicant for a broker's
14 license must have successfully completed an additional sixty hours in courses of study
15 approved by the commission. An applicant for a salesperson's or broker's license may
16 take the licensing examination before fulfillment of the prerequisite educational
17 requirement; however, the commission may not issue a salesperson's license to an
18 applicant unless satisfactory evidence of completion of this prerequisite educational
19 requirement is furnished to the commission. An applicant for a broker's license must
20 have satisfactorily fulfilled the educational requirement before taking the broker's
21 licensing examination.
22 5. If the commission finds an applicant could not acquire employment as a licensed real
23 estate salesperson because of conditions existing in the area where the salesperson
24 resides, the experience requirements established in subdivisions a and b of
25 subsection 3 may be waived by the commission. The educational requirements of
26 subsection 4 may not be waived by the commission, but guidelines may be
27 established by which applicants who have engaged in certain educational courses of
28 study which are closely related to the real estate profession may be deemed to have
29 satisfied this requirement.
30 6. The commission may adopt reasonable rules and regulations pursuant to the
31 provisions of chapter 28-32 relative to procedures for licensing, approval of
