3 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 43-23-13.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is
4 amended and reenacted as follows:
5 43-23-13.1. License renewal.
6 1. Every person licensed to practice as a real estate broker or real estate salesperson
7 shall register annually with the commission at a regular interval set by the commission
8 not less than annually and pay the appropriate annual renewal fee as provided in
9 section 43-23-13. The application for renewal must be accompanied by such
10 certification as required by this chapter and rules of the commission to show
11 compliance with the educational requirements of sections 43-23-08 and 43-23-08.2,
12 and must be submitted to the commission with the appropriate fee no later than the
13 application deadline set by the commission. A licensee that fails to file a timely
14 application for the renewal of any license and pay the renewal fee on or before the
15 application deadline set by the commission may file a late renewal application,
16 together with the required educational certification, before January fifteenth of the
17 subsequent yearon or before a date set by the commission and shall pay, in addition
18 to the renewal fee, a late fee as set by the commission for each month or fraction of a
19 month after the application deadline. Any license not renewed by January fifteenththe
20 late renewal date set by the commission must be canceled. The cancellation must be
21 performed without any notice or opportunity for hearing. Any person whose license has
22 been canceled and which desires relicensure must be required to satisfy the
23 application and examination requirements for prospective licensees in accordance
24 with this chapter and rules of the commission.
25 2. A licensee may not engage in any activity after December thirty-firstthe license
26 renewal date set by the commission of any year for which a license is required under
27 this chapter unless that person's license has been renewed by the commission.
